For installation instructions, see the INSTALL file.

For Linux 5.15 and newer, build the kernel module on a Linux host with the
matching kernel headers installed.  The updated out-of-tree build uses the
kernel's `M=` interface through the top-level Makefile in this directory.

There are serveral example programs/utilities that can be found in the utils
directory.  If you have run make tools or make install, the compiled binaries
are located in the utils/bin directory.  To install any of these utilities just 
move them to one of your PATH directories or update your path to include this 
directory.

1.0 INITIALIZE THE ESCC

    Each time the driver is loaded, the board/port must be initialized prior to 
    use.  To initialize a port, you must do at least two things: 
	1) Set the clock
	2) Set configurations
    This can be done in your program's code, or using the following utilities:

1.1 ESCCP CLOCK

    Program to set the main clock generator for the Esccp board.

    This function only works on older (not -335) hardware

	$ ./esccclock 0 frequency

    This function is for the new ESCC-PCI-335 

	$ ./setclock 0 frequency

    There is one clock per board.  Setting the clock will affect both ports on
    a single board.

1.2 ESCCP SETTINGS

    The esccpsettings program will setup the board's configuration. 

    Look at the set files (hdlcset, asyncset, bisyncset) that are included in 
    the directory of esccpsettings. Modify these files to your liking.

	$ ./esccpsettings 0 hdlcset

2.0 TESTING THE ESCC INSTALL

    After building the driver and the example programs, you can test the 
    installation of the card.  To do so you will need to build a loop back 
    plug that connects the transmitter and receiver of a port together.
    Refer to the hardware manul found on your CD at:

	/fastcom_manuals/esccpci335.pdf

    When you have the loop back built and installed, you can test port 0:

	$ cd /utils/bin
	$ ./setclock 0 6000000
	$ ./esccpsettings 0 hdlcset
	$ ./rdwr 0 0 1024 h

    Port 1:

	$ ./esccpsettings 1 hdlcset
	$ ./rdwr 1 1 1024 h

